,Recommended,305960,12909540,"Posted: 12 November, 2014",all,FeralMoonlight,"I do recommend this game, even at this stage, to people willing to put up with bugs and etc.I played it for a couple of minutes and I love the concept. I would really like to post this review to notify fellow players and mostly the developers about the things I have found. Please don't burn me down, I am not a very good gamer, but I believe I should be able to at least have a shot at any game, so here are some things that would make the game idiot-proof:1. Dragon flight speed has been greatly improved since last time I played it. Steering my dragon around now goes easily. However, I am still missing a possibility to kind of hang still in the air and possibly land like a helicopter. I am curious if there are going to be air battles and how those are going to be implemented because we are going to need a better way to brake, make sharp turns, perform acrobatics and etc. Sometimes you will simply need a sharp turn to eat that one goblin's head off!2. Camera: Is fine now, good job!3. Dragon creation screen: Yay for customisation! I realise that once the mechanics of the game are running smoothly, you can start focussing on this point. Being able to zoom in on the face and edit features would be great (look at the Elder Scrolls series, Fallout, etc). Turn your dragon around like you are sculpting it would be awesome. And genders, we need genders.4. I believe that there should eventually be a ""lock on"" option during battles and the HP bars of your target should be visible. The battles right now are just really easy: you land somewhere, goblins come running and you burn them, then eat them. Or turn them into a bloodstain and then eat them.5. SFX and music: The music is really epic, but in my opinion it would be great if the music would change depending on the situation, calm during flight and just walking around, and epic during battles and engages. The SFX are fine for a game in this stage, however you may want to make the dragon a little more menacing by e.g. adding a kind of snarling sound when he breathes fire, adding sounds of pain and agony when you are hit (same goes for the enemies).6. FPS: I have a very decent PC that can run pretty heavy games, but somehow when I play the game in high graphics, my FPS drop to levels I'd expect on my 5-year-old laptop. Low graphics work fine.7. Graphics: yeah I know these are not important yet when you are building on the mechanics, but of course the graphics need an overhaul. Ground textures are simple, characters look square. Movement of the dragon is lacking especially when running. There is no AI implemented into the enemies (yet) so they come running and start hitting you like they are suicidal. Yada yada, stuff for later.Keep up the great work, I am really looking forward to more!"
