76561198016944373,Not Recommended,305960,18849571,"Posted: 2 November, 2015",all,Rodo,"I got this game on a whim and boy do I regret that decision. First of all, the price is ridiculous, 18 dollars for a game that features floaty flying mechanics and low resolutions maps? IN ALPHA? It is an embarrassment on my part for paying for this game. The animations are goofy, the dragons themselves have so few polygons they look like something out of a PS1 game and they have the low resolution textures to match too. One of the features of the game is ""destructible environments"" where the destruction is limited to burning down some stuff like houses and trees to a crisp... in exactly the same way every single time. The fire graphics... oh my god... seriously, it's on the same level as Quake (the original one). ""Towns"" are basically agglomerations of houses sitting on the grass on some prairie or field. They don't look lived in by real people (as humans in these towns are more akin to ants than humans), they don't look like they function as towns and once you've done burning down every single building to the same texture of burnt wood there is no sense of achievement or satisfaction. Nothing you do in this game makes any difference, you might as well just do nothing at all.The only thing that seems like it might be a good idea is the concept of flight as you get to flap your own wings at your choice, this means you can control flight much better than other games where there is no difference piloting a flying animal and a jet plane. However the execution of this concept is underwhelming, it doesn't help that the flying animations are just goofy looking and mechanical.All in all, a very bad game and the developer excusing it calling out early access and alpha as some sort of excuse for the very poor quality this game has is an indication that this project will never see completion. The mechanics of the game are floaty and unappealing, the graphics are horrible, the textures are low resolution and just ugly, the effects for fire are amazingly bad (and this is a game where you'll be using fire as your main weapon mind you) and I say amazingly because there are free games out there that have better effects for fire. I don't believe this game will ever see completion and I do believe the developer is getting more money than he/she deserves by careful editing of his game's trailer.If you pay 18 dollars for this game you're either a dumbass like I am or you're using your parent's credit card and you have no sense for value of money. There are 99 cent games for smartphones that have good graphics, solid gameplay and some even have campaigns with storylines. This game has none of those features. This game is the perfect example of how payed early access can backfire and why these kinds of games should not be allowed to exist by the people over at Steam."
