,Recommended,305960,12845706,"Posted: 8 November, 2014",all,Necrodusk,"UPDATED: 14 November 2014First off, let me say that this game is in VERY Early Access. All you can really do at this time is fly around and flame some stuff, so if you're looking for a finished game, don't get this just yet. However, this game has a lot of potential, and at this point in time, looks very promising. How it goes from here depends on where the dev takes it, though they seem to genuinely enjoy doing this, so I have high hopes for how it comes out.I'll edit this as more content is released and the game is updated.Now, there are currently a number of bugs that are with the game (to be expected from early access) including:~The Exit button does not work (EDIT: The Exit button only seems to break if you delete a dragon)~If you delete a dragon after creating it, it will no longer let you choose/create new dragons, and you are stuck with the dragon you deleted. (EDIT: Completely deleting the ""Dragon"" folder in steam => steamapps => common folder on your C: drive (or wherever Steam installs itself to) and reinstalling the game seems to fix this).~After deleting the dragons and restarting the game, the ""New World"" is shaded out, until I tried to exit the game (which failed because the button was broken) and went back to the menu, where the New World option was available again, even though forcing me to play as the dragon I deleted.~There is also a case of extreme lag, especially when flaming people. (EDIT: It has been fixed, since now it isn't and endless fountain of food, but it still lags at least my game, even though it doesn't crash the game like it used to.)~An issue with the mouse staying inside of the window when in windowed mode~The camera runs a little high, especially when you land, and seems to get stuck on whatever position it had to go to when you landed.~Resolution problems, where changing the resolution affects the menus (at least in Windowed mode, not sure about fullscreen), making it difficult to navigate them because they do not size down with the res, or they compress to fit into the window without changing size, thus overlapping each other.~RPG elements are minimal, killing humans and ""eating"" the blocks they dropped increases your experience bar, even though I haven't found enough humans to get to the level up screen just yet.~Customization is minimal down to changing your dragon's color.~Perhaps moving the dragon closer to the screen when customizing so you can see them better, as well as enabling a sort of free look so as to be able to clearly see every part of the dragon you're customizing~A lot of very bad lag, don't know if it's my computer. But the moment the game starts to the monent it closes there is lag.Glitches aside, and despite its current minimal state as I'm playing it (14 Novemeber 2014 --- 7 Days after release) this game looks very promising and genuinely fun. I'm looking forward to where the devs take this."
